Run the model on a NeuronCore via **`torch-neuronx` (XLA)** in `torch.bfloat16`. There is **no eager mode** on Neuron — compile the forward with `torch_neuronx.trace` / `bucket_model_trace` at fixed shapes and call the compiled module per request (`torch_xla` placement under the hood). Do NOT run inference on CPU or in `float32` — it will be far too slow, and a CPU fallback is incorrect for this target. The first `neuronx-cc` compile of each new graph shape takes minutes, so keep shapes **static** (fixed prompt/decode buckets), pre-compile buckets at startup, and reuse the persistent compile cache so later steps hit it instead of recompiling. See the `neuron-pytorch` serving-systems reference for details.
